Notes: This column stores a free-text description or identifier for the measurement, which is best represented as a string datatype.
Patient ID is linked to the Measurement via the 'hasPatient' property, making this path semantically appropriate.
Measurement code represents a coded value for the measurement, directly mapping to 'hasCode' with a Code entity.
Measurement value is a numerical quantity, best represented as a double datatype within 'hasQuantity'.
Measurement unit specifies the unit of the measurement, mapped as part of the Quantity entity.
Measurement date is a datetime value, mapped to 'hasDateTime' with a dateTime datatype.
